│ IR.\n\n### 3. Root Cause Analysis ###\nThe root cause is in the `replaceUsesWithIf`     │
│ function, which replaces all uses of the comparison instruction without properly        │
│ checking the context of each use. Specifically, the lambda function passed to           │
│ `replaceUsesWithIf` does not account for all constraints, leading to invalid            │
│ replacements.\n\n### 4. Proposed Edit Points ###\n#### Edit Point 1:                    │
│ `llvm/lib/IR/Value.cpp` (Lines 554-583)\nModify the `replaceUsesWithIf` function to     │
│ ensure that it handles constants correctly and validates replacements more robustly.    │
│ Add additional checks to the lambda function to prevent invalid replacements.\n\n####   │
│ Edit Point 2: `llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp` (Lines             │
│ 1438-1484)\nUpdate the `ReplaceCmpWithConstant` lambda function to include stricter     │
│ checks for valid replacements. Ensure that the replacement is only applied when it is   │
│ guaranteed to be correct for all uses of the comparison instruction.\n\n### 5.          │
│ Conclusion ###\nThe proposed fixes will ensure that the transformation in the           │
│ `constraint-elimination` module only replaces comparison results when it is valid to do │
│ so, preventing incorrect transformations and Alive2 verification failures."})           │
